RACE.FOOTNOTES: JO DADDY was on heels having to be throttled down sharply behind the frontrunner who was slowing the pace down into the first turn, recovered to rate kindly behind the leaders down the backside, started to move forward shifting out three wide with a run at the quarter pole and was gaining with each stride to wear the the leaders in deep stretch for the win. BUCK'S FIZZ angled in from the outside to track in the two path in the first turn, pressed the pace outside down the backstretch, bid for the lead inching ahead at the five sixteenths marker, battled in upper stretch with a determined early leader, edged away from that foe at the sixteenth pole but could not hold off the closing in winner in the final jump before the wire. SPEEDY BULLEIT took command angling in to the rail for the lead, slowing it down when entering the first turn setting a soft pace, continued up front with mild pressure outside, was collared outside midway on the far turn, battled stubbornly on the fence for the lead until the sixteenth pole and faded late to hold for third at the wire. THOR'S CAUSE stalked near the rear on the rail in the beginning, co-trailed on the inside down the backside, asked for more edging closer with five sixteenths to run, was in range just behind the engaged leaders at the top of the stretch and finished up evenly for a minor role in the end. DUBAWI BULL was steadied going into the first bend, co-trailed on the outside down the backstretch, offered a mild run midway on the far turn, angled four wide turning for home and could not get involved driving to the finish line. TRUE SHOT was pinched between foes on the break, then was checked going into the first turn, regrouped to track two wide outside down the back straight, prompted the pace three wide at the three eighths marker, could not go on with others through the turn losing ground and was not a factor in the stretch drive. STEWARDS INQUIRY UNDER THE WIRE FOR THE FIRST TIME (15/16THS POLE) RESULTED IN #7 BUCKS FIZZ BEING DISQUALIFIED AND PLACED LAST FOR INTERFERENCE
